WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:02.516
Previously on will Trent…

2
00:00:02.540 --> 00:00:04.346
Adelaide knows where my uncle is.

3
00:00:04.370 --> 00:00:05.686
Adelaide!

4
00:00:05.710 --> 00:00:08.000
I'm sorry. bud. She's gone.

5
00:00:08.550 --> 00:00:11.776
Antonio could be dead or
worse. Nobody has any answers.

6
00:00:11.800 --> 00:00:16.196
The best way to get to
Antonio has to be Jeb oswald.

7
00:00:16.220 --> 00:00:18.736
What is Adelaide doing?

8
00:00:18.760 --> 00:00:22.036
I get my instructions from somebody
else. His name is the commander.

9
00:00:22.060 --> 00:00:24.770
- Adelaide must really trust you.
- We understand each other.

10
00:00:25.690 --> 00:00:26.996
- What's this?
- We'll be in touch.

11
00:00:27.020 --> 00:00:29.246
You have no sightings
of Adelaide trevens?

12
00:00:29.270 --> 00:00:31.836
No. it has not rung yet.

13
00:00:31.860 --> 00:00:33.756
He's my family. ange.

14
00:00:33.780 --> 00:00:34.780
They're gonna find him.

15
00:00:42.700 --> 00:00:45.290
Help! Help me.

16
00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:53.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

17
00:01:24.620 --> 00:01:25.620
No drugs.

18
00:01:28.540 --> 00:01:32.436
Just a student ID and a library card.

19
00:01:32.460 --> 00:01:36.486
We've got stolen mail.
fraudulent loan applications.

20
00:01:36.510 --> 00:01:39.140
Sweet Dylan Rome.
What are you doing here?

21
00:01:40.970 --> 00:01:43.640
Well. this room's a DNA nightmare.

22
00:01:46.730 --> 00:01:48.560
- Let's get these bagged.
- All right.

23
00:01:51.360 --> 00:01:52.560
Let's follow this blood trail.

24
00:02:07.790 --> 00:02:09.120
Two more casings right here.

25
00:02:12.090 --> 00:02:13.800
9-mil. same caliber.

26
00:02:15.300 --> 00:02:17.236
Hey. let's make sure we
get these bagged up too.

27
00:02:17.260 --> 00:02:18.470
Yeah. there's a trail.

28
00:02:23.850 --> 00:02:25.286
Shooter had to come this way.

29
00:02:25.310 --> 00:02:28.060
The evidence techs are gonna
have a blast bagging up all this trash.

30
00:02:29.020 --> 00:02:30.746
That bench has your
name all over it. Franklin.

31
00:02:30.770 --> 00:02:32.150
No. looks better in your house.

32
00:02:36.990 --> 00:02:38.860
Jackpot.

33
00:02:40.280 --> 00:02:42.546
Brand-new video game
system out here all by itself.

34
00:02:42.570 --> 00:02:44.176
You think that's Dylan's blood on it?

35
00:02:44.200 --> 00:02:46.926
I mean. no. Otherwise.
how did he end up inside?

36
00:02:46.950 --> 00:02:49.830
Maybe Dylan was shooting at someone
trying to steal a video game system.

37
00:02:50.370 --> 00:02:51.540
That kid is not a killer.

38
00:02:52.630 --> 00:02:54.266
Maybe we found our second victim.

39
00:02:54.290 --> 00:02:55.590
Could still be alive.

40
00:02:56.550 --> 00:02:59.470
- Hey. let's bag this.
- You got it.

41
00:03:00.300 --> 00:03:03.116
No one here is gonna tell us anything.

42
00:03:03.140 --> 00:03:04.300
Well. there is that guy.

43
00:03:06.770 --> 00:03:08.060
Can't hurt to try.

44
00:03:09.600 --> 00:03:10.980
It absolutely can.

45
00:03:14.310 --> 00:03:15.400
Excuse me. sir.

46
00:03:15.900 --> 00:03:18.070
The shooting. you see what happened?

47
00:03:18.570 --> 00:03:19.950
No. sir. I'm blind.

48
00:03:20.700 --> 00:03:23.176
Great. Let's pull whatever
camera footage we can find.

49
00:03:23.200 --> 00:03:25.080
Hold up. we got a witness right here.

50
00:03:25.580 --> 00:03:27.636
The witness didn't see anything. literally.

51
00:03:27.660 --> 00:03:28.806
Yeah. but he's blind.

52
00:03:28.830 --> 00:03:30.636
That's exactly what I just said.

53
00:03:30.660 --> 00:03:31.960
Haven't you heard of daredevil?

54
00:03:32.540 --> 00:03:33.936
Maybe his senses got sharper.

55
00:03:33.960 --> 00:03:35.686
The man got ears. a nose.

56
00:03:35.710 --> 00:03:38.606
Kid you're looking for
ran for his life. got shot.

57
00:03:38.630 --> 00:03:41.430
Some good samaritan scooped him up.

58
00:03:44.850 --> 00:03:46.720
Did you happen to see…

59
00:03:48.270 --> 00:03:50.350
- Any idea who pulled the trigger?
- Not here.

60
00:03:51.730 --> 00:03:54.916
- Maybe you buy Mac a sandwich first?
- Yeah. okay. Franklin?

61
00:03:54.940 --> 00:03:56.980
I'ma start calling hospitals.
You take his order.

62
00:04:01.650 --> 00:04:03.290
What do you want.
like. a ham and cheese?

63
00:04:03.860 --> 00:04:05.200
Not if you want me to talk.

64
00:04:05.740 --> 00:04:08.636
That's ridiculous. How can
they say there's no metadata?

65
00:04:08.660 --> 00:04:10.136
There's always metadata.

66
00:04:10.160 --> 00:04:12.726
That's the whole point of metadata.

67
00:04:12.750 --> 00:04:14.096
They're the FBI.

68
00:04:14.120 --> 00:04:16.606
You think I'm holding out on you?

69
00:04:16.630 --> 00:04:20.396
Caroline. is there any new
intel on Adelaide trevens

70
00:04:20.420 --> 00:04:22.316
that we have not forwarded
to special agent Trent?

71
00:04:22.340 --> 00:04:25.616
No. ma'am. you gave me clear
instructions to share everything.

72
00:04:25.640 --> 00:04:28.866
- I've kept a spreadsheet.
- I appreciate it. Caroline. Thank you.

73
00:04:28.890 --> 00:04:30.536
You just mad she's making you wait.

74
00:04:30.560 --> 00:04:34.036
I mean. why give me a phone
if she's not going to use it?

75
00:04:34.060 --> 00:04:36.520
He's alive. will. You and I both know that.

76
00:04:39.020 --> 00:04:41.046
- Printed copy of your speech.
- Thanks.

77
00:04:41.070 --> 00:04:42.240
Speech?

78
00:04:42.360 --> 00:04:43.716
Deputy director Wagner…

79
00:04:43.740 --> 00:04:45.256
…is giving a speech at
a leadership conference

80
00:04:45.280 --> 00:04:47.346
with some very important people.

81
00:04:47.370 --> 00:04:50.966
It's just a hotel ballroom.
Sad lettuce and weak coffee.

82
00:04:50.990 --> 00:04:53.346
With some very impressive people.

83
00:04:53.370 --> 00:04:55.146
Well. I'm very impressed.

84
00:04:55.170 --> 00:04:57.056
I keep telling you. you should be.

85
00:04:57.080 --> 00:04:58.646
Okay. I'm going.

86
00:04:58.670 --> 00:05:01.856
If that Adelaide phone rings.
I am leaving wherever I am.

87
00:05:01.880 --> 00:05:03.026
no matter who's there.

88
00:05:03.050 --> 00:05:05.566
- You understand?
- Yeah. who else am I gonna call?

89
00:05:05.590 --> 00:05:06.680
I keep telling you.

90
00:05:24.990 --> 00:05:26.610
I ruined the potatoes.

91
00:05:28.490 --> 00:05:29.490
Nico.

92
00:05:30.740 --> 00:05:32.806
What happened? Let me see.

93
00:05:32.830 --> 00:05:34.846
- It's not that bad.
- It is that bad.

94
00:05:34.870 --> 00:05:36.686
I see bone. Keep it elevated.

95
00:05:36.710 --> 00:05:38.936
No. that's potato.

96
00:05:38.960 --> 00:05:40.856
No. it's not. Okay? You
got to keep it elevated.

97
00:05:40.880 --> 00:05:43.210
- We're going to the er.
- Tell Betty I love her.

98
00:05:44.050 --> 00:05:45.970
Okay. Come on. Nico.

99
00:05:48.800 --> 00:05:50.100
She has hair.

100
00:05:51.430 --> 00:05:53.520
I hope she's a redhead.

101
00:05:54.270 --> 00:05:56.560
There's hair inside my uterus.

102
00:05:57.690 --> 00:05:59.496
- It's gross.
- Absolutely.

103
00:05:59.520 --> 00:06:01.246
- Right?
- Yeah. But also amazing.

104
00:06:01.270 --> 00:06:02.876
- I mean. right?
- I mean. yeah. It is. I mean…

105
00:06:02.900 --> 00:06:05.530
If you think that's gross. just wait.

106
00:06:08.450 --> 00:06:11.910
Try to enjoy this time. It's
the calm before the storm.

107
00:06:12.700 --> 00:06:14.200
Thank you. Dr. Gundis. We will.

108
00:06:16.160 --> 00:06:17.226
Sorry.

109
00:06:17.250 --> 00:06:18.936
Hey. they made it almost the full hour.

110
00:06:18.960 --> 00:06:20.266
Almost.

111
00:06:20.290 --> 00:06:21.856
"Bus accident." We got to go.

112
00:06:21.880 --> 00:06:24.566
So from here on out. I want
to see you every week. okay?

113
00:06:24.590 --> 00:06:27.856
Just to make sure your sweet
little angel is happy and healthy.

114
00:06:27.880 --> 00:06:29.300
And it's time for desk duty.

115
00:06:29.930 --> 00:06:32.906
So soon. I thought you could
make it another month or two.

116
00:06:32.930 --> 00:06:34.616
you know. maybe through labor...

117
00:06:34.640 --> 00:06:36.890
- it's fine. I'm ready. I can do it.
- Okay.

118
00:06:49.320 --> 00:06:52.466
- Excuse me. I need Dr. Chambliss.
- I'll see if I can find him.

119
00:06:52.490 --> 00:06:54.780
Tell him it's about
Kevin's eyes. It's urgent.

120
00:06:55.740 --> 00:06:58.476
I don't know who this
is worse for. you or Nico.

121
00:06:58.500 --> 00:07:00.596
Woman. it was an emergency. okay?

122
00:07:00.620 --> 00:07:03.646
And in case you forgot. I can't read.

123
00:07:03.670 --> 00:07:06.646
so I went to the one place
I know how to get to. Just…

124
00:07:06.670 --> 00:07:09.196
Big mistake. You'll just get
sick sitting in the waiting room.

125
00:07:09.220 --> 00:07:12.446
and you'll end up in urgent care. where
you should've went in the first place.

126
00:07:12.470 --> 00:07:13.760
Yeah. whatever.

127
00:07:14.470 --> 00:07:16.100
Here. I got you.

128
00:07:17.270 --> 00:07:19.366
It's… what?

129
00:07:19.390 --> 00:07:22.480
Who's helping you? I bet it's
not anyone with medical training.

130
00:07:24.230 --> 00:07:25.746
Okay. Much obliged.

131
00:07:25.770 --> 00:07:27.626
Down with king George.

132
00:07:27.650 --> 00:07:30.966
Okay. I'll call you when I get out of here.

133
00:07:30.990 --> 00:07:32.756
I'll talk to you in 20 years.

134
00:07:32.780 --> 00:07:33.870
Ha ha.

135
00:07:43.750 --> 00:07:46.420
- It's a madhouse today?
- Just another Tuesday.

136
00:07:49.710 --> 00:07:51.066
You have to hold it.

137
00:07:51.090 --> 00:07:53.736
- I know. but you've gotta hold it.
- What are you doing here?

138
00:07:53.760 --> 00:07:55.736
Hey. Seth and I had baby stuff upstairs.

139
00:07:55.760 --> 00:07:57.890
- Wait. No.
- Hey.

140
00:08:00.060 --> 00:08:01.406
Give it.

141
00:08:01.430 --> 00:08:04.626
Hey. how did you let this happen? I
told you to get rid of that man do line.

142
00:08:04.650 --> 00:08:07.020
A man do line is an excellent
tool when used safely.

143
00:08:07.650 --> 00:08:09.610
Are you blaming the victim?

144
00:08:10.280 --> 00:08:11.876
And why is it called a man do line?

145
00:08:11.900 --> 00:08:13.296
You prefer "they-them-do line"?

146
00:08:13.320 --> 00:08:14.740
How about a "cut-your-hand-oline"?

147
00:08:16.410 --> 00:08:19.016
Dr. Chambliss? I need
to talk to Dr. Chambliss.

148
00:08:19.040 --> 00:08:21.636
- Please stay in the room...
- why isn't anybody listening to me?

149
00:08:21.660 --> 00:08:24.226
I need to speak to Dr. Chambliss.
There's something wrong with my son...

150
00:08:24.250 --> 00:08:25.920
he is making his rounds right now.

151
00:08:26.540 --> 00:08:30.026
Dr. Chambliss. Kevin's
eyes are still moving.

152
00:08:30.050 --> 00:08:31.816
You told me that they would stop.

153
00:08:31.840 --> 00:08:34.606
Something is wrong. I'm
telling you. it's a seizure.

154
00:08:34.630 --> 00:08:36.550
Your son is fine. He's stable.

155
00:08:37.050 --> 00:08:38.406
It's normal for his eyes to move.

156
00:08:38.430 --> 00:08:41.496
As I've explained. he's been sedated
so the bullet in his neck stays put

157
00:08:41.520 --> 00:08:42.956
until we can move him to surgery.

158
00:08:42.980 --> 00:08:46.246
As I explained. he gets seizures.

159
00:08:46.270 --> 00:08:49.166
I know people like you don't
like to listen to people like me.

160
00:08:49.190 --> 00:08:51.876
but if you don't. he's
gonna get brain damage.

161
00:08:51.900 --> 00:08:54.006
I'm his mother. I know that
there is something wrong.

162
00:08:54.030 --> 00:08:56.296
I'm his doctor. I'll take a look
at him when I have a chance.

163
00:08:56.320 --> 00:08:58.950
- Hey. don't you walk away from me.
- Look. you can leave.

164
00:09:00.830 --> 00:09:03.176
Or you can explain to social
services why your pupils are dilated.

165
00:09:03.200 --> 00:09:05.436
- Why won't you listen to me?
- How about we get some air?

166
00:09:05.460 --> 00:09:08.646
Get your hands off of me! You are cooking
his brain. You're gonna let him die.

167
00:09:08.670 --> 00:09:11.736
He is stable. we are helping him. You
don't know what you're talking about.

168
00:09:11.760 --> 00:09:14.566
Excuse me. I'm special
agent will Trent with the gbi.

169
00:09:14.590 --> 00:09:16.066
Great. Get her out of here.

170
00:09:16.090 --> 00:09:17.550
"Get her out of here"?

171
00:09:18.140 --> 00:09:19.986
Whoa!

172
00:09:20.010 --> 00:09:21.770
Down. get down.

173
00:09:22.850 --> 00:09:25.850
Nobody leaves until my son gets help.

174
00:09:34.780 --> 00:09:35.860
Great sandwich.

175
00:09:37.110 --> 00:09:39.780
You know. most places don't
soak the bread crumbs. so…

176
00:09:40.740 --> 00:09:42.056
Then the meatballs get tough.

177
00:09:42.080 --> 00:09:44.306
You know. Mac. you
kind of agreed to tell us

178
00:09:44.330 --> 00:09:46.290
what you know when we
bought you that sandwich.

179
00:09:52.710 --> 00:09:55.130
I can't do this.

180
00:09:58.800 --> 00:10:00.156
Any time. man.

181
00:10:00.180 --> 00:10:01.486
Just before Jesus comes back.

182
00:10:04.560 --> 00:10:07.270
Osiris. Real scary dude.

183
00:10:08.900 --> 00:10:10.666
He took over the block
about a month ago.

184
00:10:10.690 --> 00:10:12.496
and since then it's been hot.

185
00:10:12.520 --> 00:10:15.530
Hot like the equator in
August. you understand?

186
00:10:16.150 --> 00:10:19.360
You see. anybody can
plant their flag in the mud.

187
00:10:20.160 --> 00:10:22.910
But it takes time for that
flag to stand on its own.

188
00:10:23.870 --> 00:10:25.556
The mud needs to dry. you feel me?

189
00:10:25.580 --> 00:10:28.710
So osiris is trying to prove to
everyone in town he's not a punk.

190
00:10:29.370 --> 00:10:30.896
As a result. he's been extra violent.

191
00:10:30.920 --> 00:10:33.670
Arm for a hand. a head for an eye.

192
00:10:34.170 --> 00:10:36.590
Forget precedent.
This is "prece-don't-try."

193
00:10:37.720 --> 00:10:40.696
But that's what it takes. you understand?

194
00:10:40.720 --> 00:10:42.116
Yeah. we understand.

195
00:10:42.140 --> 00:10:43.140
Amen.

196
00:10:46.520 --> 00:10:49.310
A-Amen.

197
00:10:51.480 --> 00:10:53.060
- Amen.
- Amen.

198
00:10:55.070 --> 00:10:59.256
So as I was saying. I hear those
two boys going to that trap house.

199
00:10:59.280 --> 00:11:01.426
Couldn't have been long
before I started hearing gunshots.

200
00:11:01.450 --> 00:11:04.280
One of them come running
out yelling. "help me. help!"

201
00:11:05.370 --> 00:11:08.450
Innocent as a dove. before "bang. bang!"

202
00:11:10.040 --> 00:11:11.540
Thoughts and prayers. you understand?

203
00:11:13.130 --> 00:11:14.920
- Y'all got any more ice?
- No.

204
00:11:16.000 --> 00:11:17.686
Now. do you think those kids was trying

205
00:11:17.710 --> 00:11:19.856
to steal the video game
system from osiris?

206
00:11:19.880 --> 00:11:21.866
If they were. they learned their lesson.

207
00:11:21.890 --> 00:11:24.616
And you can bet osiris left it there

208
00:11:24.640 --> 00:11:27.156
so everybody else can learn theirs too.

209
00:11:27.180 --> 00:11:29.786
It's a flag in the mud.

210
00:11:29.810 --> 00:11:31.690
Y'all better find that boy who got away.

211
00:11:32.520 --> 00:11:34.400
If he ain't dead yet. he will be soon.

212
00:11:36.440 --> 00:11:38.110
Can y'all take me to get some cigarettes?

213
00:11:38.860 --> 00:11:40.676
- It's right up the street.
- Absolutely not.

214
00:11:40.700 --> 00:11:42.636
- If y'all don't mind.
- No. no. we mind.

215
00:11:51.580 --> 00:11:53.780
Let me know if there's
anything else you want me to do.

216
00:12:01.010 --> 00:12:02.010
Hey. you okay?

217
00:12:03.970 --> 00:12:05.850
I don't know. Are we?

218
00:12:06.550 --> 00:12:09.060
Yeah. as long as we stay calm.

219
00:12:14.400 --> 00:12:15.996
Hey. Hey.

220
00:12:17.650 --> 00:12:18.980
Just take deep breaths.

221
00:12:24.570 --> 00:12:26.966
- You help him!
- Okay. I'm gonna check your son's chart.

222
00:12:26.990 --> 00:12:28.676
but first. tell me what I should know.

223
00:12:28.700 --> 00:12:32.016
That doctor said he was stable.
and then his eyes started fluttering.

224
00:12:32.040 --> 00:12:35.096
It's not normal. I know it's
not normal. Look at his eyes.

225
00:12:35.120 --> 00:12:36.790
Okay. let's keep the gun on me.

226
00:12:37.420 --> 00:12:39.936
I'm the one you need to
worry about. right? Gbi.

227
00:12:39.960 --> 00:12:43.066
So we ran a ct scan and
checked for internal bleeding.

228
00:12:43.090 --> 00:12:44.566
Both came back negative.

229
00:12:44.590 --> 00:12:46.446
And we sedated him.

230
00:12:46.470 --> 00:12:49.576
- Does Kevin have a history of seizures?
- Yes. it happened when he was a kid.

231
00:12:49.600 --> 00:12:52.206
- "Status" something.
- Mom's right. Status epileptic us.

232
00:12:52.230 --> 00:12:54.730
I can stop it with medication.
but I need my resident. okay?

233
00:12:55.520 --> 00:12:57.980
Dr. Rosen?

234
00:12:58.560 --> 00:13:00.820
Give me a loading dose of
Keppra and two of Lorazepam.

235
00:13:01.400 --> 00:13:02.796
It's down the hall.

236
00:13:02.820 --> 00:13:05.070
- Is that okay?
- You have one minute.

237
00:13:05.700 --> 00:13:08.280
And can someone shut that woman up?

238
00:13:08.530 --> 00:13:12.386
Okay. nakia. you have a
doctor who's listening to you.

239
00:13:12.410 --> 00:13:15.096
He has a plan to stop the
seizures. You were right.

240
00:13:15.120 --> 00:13:16.960
There's no need for the
gun anymore. is there?

241
00:13:20.000 --> 00:13:21.840
You're okay.

242
00:13:22.960 --> 00:13:26.840
Woman. if you don't shut
your damn mouth! Shut up!

243
00:13:27.470 --> 00:13:29.680
Watch it. gbi. Back up.

244
00:13:30.260 --> 00:13:33.076
The only reason why
you listen to me is this.

245
00:13:33.100 --> 00:13:36.116
and I'm not gonna let it go
until I know that Kevin is okay.

246
00:13:36.140 --> 00:13:37.416
That's where we are.

247
00:13:37.440 --> 00:13:40.626
- Okay.
- We're out of Lorazepam.

248
00:13:40.650 --> 00:13:43.206
and I can't get into the pharmacy
because we're code silver.

249
00:13:43.230 --> 00:13:44.506
I don't know what to do.

250
00:13:44.530 --> 00:13:47.426
What do you mean you're out?
Find something else. Help him.

251
00:13:47.450 --> 00:13:49.466
Seth. where else could it be?

252
00:13:49.490 --> 00:13:51.030
An ambulance would have it.

253
00:13:51.660 --> 00:13:52.950
Okay. there you go.

254
00:13:53.700 --> 00:13:55.176
SWAT's gonna be outside.

255
00:13:55.200 --> 00:13:58.346
They can deliver it.
All we need to do is ask.

256
00:13:58.370 --> 00:14:00.726
SWAT? You're lying.

257
00:14:00.750 --> 00:14:02.920
Nakia. look at me.

258
00:14:03.760 --> 00:14:05.396
You have hostages.

259
00:14:05.420 --> 00:14:07.856
That means SWAT's here. It's protocol.

260
00:14:07.880 --> 00:14:10.510
Everyone wants Kevin to be okay.

261
00:14:11.600 --> 00:14:14.100
I know exactly how this goes.

262
00:14:14.930 --> 00:14:17.060
They've already cut the phone lines.

263
00:14:33.790 --> 00:14:35.410
Hey. what's the status?

264
00:14:36.120 --> 00:14:38.636
Phone lines are cut.
evac is almost complete.

265
00:14:38.660 --> 00:14:40.266
and exits have been secured.

266
00:14:40.290 --> 00:14:42.566
Okay. good. Let's keep
digging on that patient manifest

267
00:14:42.590 --> 00:14:44.226
and get nakia cane a sat phone.

268
00:14:44.250 --> 00:14:45.486
I'd like to say hello.

269
00:14:45.510 --> 00:14:46.566
Yes. ma'am.

270
00:14:46.590 --> 00:14:47.840
Phone.

271
00:14:52.970 --> 00:14:54.100
I got this.

272
00:14:55.560 --> 00:14:57.230
Shh…

273
00:15:00.900 --> 00:15:03.610
What is that?

274
00:15:04.610 --> 00:15:05.730
That's your sat phone.

275
00:15:06.820 --> 00:15:08.070
It's gonna ring in a second.

276
00:15:11.530 --> 00:15:13.886
Nakia. you have a very small window

277
00:15:13.910 --> 00:15:15.670
when the people
outside are willing to help.

278
00:15:16.120 --> 00:15:19.870
After that. they're gonna cut the power.
and Kevin needs these machines to work.

279
00:15:20.790 --> 00:15:24.290
Dr. Mcdale. how long until doc's
injury turns into a murder charge?

280
00:15:24.840 --> 00:15:25.936
Not long.

281
00:15:25.960 --> 00:15:29.380
Kevin needs Lorazepam. Doc
needs saving. You have the gun.

282
00:15:31.430 --> 00:15:32.986
I'm gonna answer the phone.

283
00:15:45.610 --> 00:15:47.626
- Trent.
- I told you to go to urgent care.

284
00:15:47.650 --> 00:15:48.706
How's it going in there?

285
00:15:48.730 --> 00:15:51.126
She needs iv Lorazepam for her son.

286
00:15:51.150 --> 00:15:53.490
- Is she gonna use that gun again?
- If she has to.

287
00:15:53.990 --> 00:15:56.506
You've got four kids
inside with you. is that right?

288
00:15:56.530 --> 00:15:57.766
Six.

289
00:15:57.790 --> 00:15:59.386
Let me talk to her.

290
00:15:59.410 --> 00:16:02.346
Will. she hit his femoral.
Tell Seth we need blood.

291
00:16:02.370 --> 00:16:03.766
Is that Angie?

292
00:16:05.380 --> 00:16:06.840
Yep. it's a party.

293
00:16:08.300 --> 00:16:11.840
Nakia cane. this is my partner.
special agent faith Mitchell.

294
00:16:12.470 --> 00:16:13.930
How's it going in there. nakia?

295
00:16:15.220 --> 00:16:17.470
I understand that your
son needs Lorazepam.

296
00:16:18.310 --> 00:16:20.810
You've got six kids in that waiting room.

297
00:16:21.520 --> 00:16:23.020
How about we make a trade?

298
00:16:30.900 --> 00:16:33.780
Come on. nakia. Everyone wins here.

299
00:16:39.660 --> 00:16:41.790
Make it fast and don't do anything stupid.

300
00:16:45.790 --> 00:16:49.920
- I need iv Lorazepam. now.
- Sergeant. Go check with…

301
00:16:51.760 --> 00:16:53.050
All right.

302
00:16:54.590 --> 00:16:56.140
Snug as a bug in a rug.

303
00:16:57.680 --> 00:16:58.760
Ready to go?

304
00:16:59.760 --> 00:17:01.680
All right.

305
00:17:02.890 --> 00:17:06.246
Is this your sloth? Can't
leave without your sloth.

306
00:17:06.270 --> 00:17:07.536
His name is Leon.

307
00:17:09.400 --> 00:17:12.126
Of course it is. Hello. Leon.

308
00:17:12.150 --> 00:17:15.676
I know sloths like you are
very. very good at hanging on.

309
00:17:15.700 --> 00:17:18.570
I'm gonna need the two of you to
hang on tight to each other. okay?

310
00:17:19.530 --> 00:17:20.580
Here you go.

311
00:17:22.370 --> 00:17:24.226
All right. I'm gonna
follow your lead. okay?

312
00:17:24.250 --> 00:17:25.870
All right. Here we go.

313
00:17:26.370 --> 00:17:27.460
Come on.

314
00:17:36.130 --> 00:17:37.130
Hey.

315
00:17:38.050 --> 00:17:39.350
What is that. a Cannon?

316
00:17:39.930 --> 00:17:40.930
No.

317
00:17:41.970 --> 00:17:43.430
It's an antique swivel gun.

318
00:17:44.060 --> 00:17:47.536
It hasn't been fired in 200
years. and it's not very accurate.

319
00:17:47.560 --> 00:17:49.706
but someone has to do something.

320
00:17:49.730 --> 00:17:52.166
And we won the siege
of fort ticonderoga.

321
00:17:52.190 --> 00:17:55.256
That was pretend.
Someone is doing something.

322
00:17:55.280 --> 00:17:58.700
Put that away right now. I'm a cop.

323
00:18:00.120 --> 00:18:04.016
Nico. this is Marshall and his sloth Leon.

324
00:18:04.040 --> 00:18:05.726
- What's up. Marshall?
- Hi.

325
00:18:05.750 --> 00:18:07.846
Did you know sloths only
poop one time a week?

326
00:18:07.870 --> 00:18:11.016
Lorazepam first. and then the kids.

327
00:18:11.040 --> 00:18:12.396
That's the plan.

328
00:18:12.420 --> 00:18:15.920
If anybody tries to run.
I'll shoot. Is that clear?

329
00:18:19.140 --> 00:18:20.140
Yeah.

330
00:18:24.680 --> 00:18:27.246
All right. Everybody's doing really great.

331
00:18:27.270 --> 00:18:28.560
We're gonna get you out of here.

332
00:18:31.690 --> 00:18:33.820
I should get this on board.
Every second matters.

333
00:18:36.190 --> 00:18:37.490
Okay. now the kids.

334
00:18:38.740 --> 00:18:41.740
Okay. here we go. Let's
go. Let's go. Come on.

335
00:18:42.410 --> 00:18:44.846
Come on. yeah. Here we go. Good job.

336
00:18:44.870 --> 00:18:46.386
To your right. Yep. there you go.

337
00:18:46.410 --> 00:18:48.766
Mcdale. you got everything
you need from outside?

338
00:18:48.790 --> 00:18:50.790
- Yeah. this should do it.
- Good.

339
00:18:54.250 --> 00:18:55.646
- Come on.
- Okay. Take it easy.

340
00:18:55.670 --> 00:18:58.130
Don't try anything or
he's not coming back.

341
00:19:12.730 --> 00:19:14.730
Lady knows how to make a point.

342
00:19:15.980 --> 00:19:18.046
Okay. okay. okay. All right. all right.

343
00:19:26.330 --> 00:19:28.266
Explain again why I can't keep this?

344
00:19:28.290 --> 00:19:30.136
It's evidence. There's blood on it.

345
00:19:30.160 --> 00:19:32.790
- Evidence that you're mean?
- Just help me turn it on.

346
00:19:34.290 --> 00:19:35.646
Yeah.

347
00:19:35.670 --> 00:19:37.936
I'm on hold. Osiris is an alias.

348
00:19:37.960 --> 00:19:40.316
No leads on his real name yet.
but I got a ci who's got his number.

349
00:19:40.340 --> 00:19:41.406
I'm trying to trace it.

350
00:19:41.430 --> 00:19:44.446
I can't believe y'all drink
tap water. Can I have this?

351
00:19:44.470 --> 00:19:45.946
That's faith's. Put it back.

352
00:19:45.970 --> 00:19:48.036
She would want me to have it.

353
00:19:48.060 --> 00:19:49.430
Hello. What you got?

354
00:19:51.940 --> 00:19:53.326
It works.

355
00:19:53.350 --> 00:19:56.416
Great. How do we find
out who owns this machine?

356
00:19:56.440 --> 00:19:59.166
It's not a machine. It's a system.

357
00:19:59.190 --> 00:20:01.176
Fifty bucks. you answer the question.

358
00:20:01.200 --> 00:20:02.450
Easy. It's right there.

359
00:20:03.030 --> 00:20:05.926
"Kevcan3!"

360
00:20:05.950 --> 00:20:07.306
And his email's underneath it.

361
00:20:07.330 --> 00:20:08.886
Twenty bucks. That was too easy.

362
00:20:08.910 --> 00:20:10.136
Fifty dollars. old man.

363
00:20:10.160 --> 00:20:14.170
Kevcan3@midtownersmail.com

364
00:20:15.500 --> 00:20:16.816
- hey. Franklin.
- Yeah.

365
00:20:16.840 --> 00:20:19.486
- I got something.
- Please tell me it's osiris's real name.

366
00:20:19.510 --> 00:20:22.590
No. but this machine
belongs to Kevin cane.

367
00:20:24.970 --> 00:20:27.026
Isn't that the name of the
kid in the hostage situation?

368
00:20:27.050 --> 00:20:30.406
- Right. That is not good.
- Why? We found our second victim.

369
00:20:30.430 --> 00:20:32.536
I still have no idea
what osiris's real name is

370
00:20:32.560 --> 00:20:33.866
or what he looks like.

371
00:20:33.890 --> 00:20:36.666
but guess where his cell phone
pinged an hour ago and it's still there?

372
00:20:36.690 --> 00:20:38.206
Please don't say St. Peter's.

373
00:20:38.230 --> 00:20:41.740
St. Peter's. We got to tell
faith before osiris kills Kevin.

374
00:20:42.320 --> 00:20:43.320
Max. go to bed.

375
00:20:52.620 --> 00:20:56.186
So osiris must have got trapped in
there when nakia locked the place down.

376
00:20:56.210 --> 00:20:59.476
Looking to make a name for himself.
and now he's caged in surrounded by cops.

377
00:20:59.500 --> 00:21:02.066
Great. This just got twice as dangerous.

378
00:21:02.090 --> 00:21:03.526
We need to tell will.

379
00:21:03.550 --> 00:21:04.736
What about a sat phone?

380
00:21:04.760 --> 00:21:06.800
She's not much of a phone girl.

381
00:21:07.390 --> 00:21:09.510
Okay. Pizza party?

382
00:21:11.470 --> 00:21:12.850
I know Angie's order.

383
00:21:19.400 --> 00:21:22.230
All right. it's gonna take a little
while before we see the results.

384
00:21:22.740 --> 00:21:25.320
- That's it?
- To stop his seizures. yes.

385
00:21:25.950 --> 00:21:27.756
Dr. Rosen and I would
like to use that time

386
00:21:27.780 --> 00:21:29.136
to check on the other patients.

387
00:21:29.160 --> 00:21:30.716
Everyone in that room needs help too.

388
00:21:30.740 --> 00:21:33.080
It's all happening. nakia.
the way you wanted.

389
00:21:33.700 --> 00:21:36.306
How about we get these
people off the floor and looked at?

390
00:21:36.330 --> 00:21:39.316
Stay where I can see you.

391
00:21:39.340 --> 00:21:41.170
Thank you. Thank you.

392
00:21:49.800 --> 00:21:50.810
So…

393
00:21:53.020 --> 00:21:55.140
What's gonna happen after this?

394
00:21:55.940 --> 00:21:59.400
I mean. I shot someone. I'm going to jail.

395
00:22:01.900 --> 00:22:03.360
I didn't want any of this.

396
00:22:04.110 --> 00:22:05.110
It's just…

397
00:22:05.950 --> 00:22:07.256
They wouldn't hear me.

398
00:22:07.280 --> 00:22:08.530
I know.

399
00:22:11.910 --> 00:22:12.950
Where'd you serve?

400
00:22:14.910 --> 00:22:15.976
I see the way you move.

401
00:22:16.000 --> 00:22:17.846
You're awfully comfortable
with that sidearm.

402
00:22:17.870 --> 00:22:19.120
You barely put your back to me.

403
00:22:20.460 --> 00:22:22.840
So where'd you serve?

404
00:22:23.590 --> 00:22:24.590
Kuwait.

405
00:22:25.710 --> 00:22:27.356
With the push in Iraq.

406
00:22:27.380 --> 00:22:30.026
Went to jump school. had a bad jump.

407
00:22:30.050 --> 00:22:31.350
Then painkillers.

408
00:22:33.560 --> 00:22:34.810
Then other stuff.

409
00:22:35.430 --> 00:22:37.020
I'm sorry it went that way for you.

410
00:22:41.980 --> 00:22:43.150
He's a good kid.

411
00:22:51.990 --> 00:22:53.530
Wants to be an engineer.

412
00:22:55.450 --> 00:22:56.830
Deserves a better mother.

413
00:22:57.540 --> 00:23:01.210
I don't know many parents who
would hold an emergency room hostage.

414
00:23:03.590 --> 00:23:06.630
It's all my fault. I've gotten real bad lately.

415
00:23:07.510 --> 00:23:10.680
I've had to start selling things.

416
00:23:11.720 --> 00:23:13.050
Our things.

417
00:23:13.680 --> 00:23:17.180
You know. when I sold all his
video games. he wasn't even mad.

418
00:23:17.680 --> 00:23:19.350
He said he understood.

419
00:23:21.600 --> 00:23:23.060
That broke my heart.

420
00:23:24.110 --> 00:23:25.610
Did he go back to get it?

421
00:23:28.190 --> 00:23:29.360
Is that what happened?

422
00:23:31.160 --> 00:23:34.780
I know exactly what it
feels like to be the reason…

423
00:23:35.620 --> 00:23:37.580
Your loved ones end up in harm's way.

424
00:23:40.080 --> 00:23:42.670
Shame. Guilt.

425
00:23:44.340 --> 00:23:45.340
Anger.

426
00:23:50.670 --> 00:23:51.680
It's terrible.

427
00:23:53.680 --> 00:23:55.300
I don't care what happens to me

428
00:23:55.930 --> 00:23:57.390
as long as he pulls through.

429
00:23:57.890 --> 00:23:59.076
Kevin will wake up.

430
00:23:59.100 --> 00:24:01.980
And when he does. I'll
make sure he stays safe.

431
00:24:03.270 --> 00:24:05.690
That's what happens
when this is all over.

432
00:24:08.980 --> 00:24:10.046
What now?

433
00:24:10.070 --> 00:24:11.966
That would be the food.

434
00:24:15.740 --> 00:24:18.136
I got plain. He's got mushroom.

435
00:24:18.160 --> 00:24:19.160
Here you go.

436
00:24:19.700 --> 00:24:21.726
Hey. honey. How's desk duty?

437
00:24:21.750 --> 00:24:25.766
So good. So relaxing. …

438
00:24:25.790 --> 00:24:28.380
Really couldn't be better.
honestly. And how was your day?

439
00:24:28.960 --> 00:24:32.050
You know. just soaking up this
quality time before the baby comes.

440
00:24:32.590 --> 00:24:34.220
Calm before the storm.

441
00:24:34.840 --> 00:24:36.430
You and will gonna save the day?

442
00:24:37.350 --> 00:24:38.470
I think we might.

443
00:24:39.560 --> 00:24:43.576
Who wants pepperoni? And
we got "pickle and pineapple"?

444
00:24:43.600 --> 00:24:46.916
That's me. That's for me.
That's for me. That's for me.

445
00:24:46.940 --> 00:24:48.246
Okay. okay. Thank you.

446
00:24:48.270 --> 00:24:51.046
Do you have matches.
or a lighter. or something?

447
00:24:51.070 --> 00:24:52.756
Knock it off.

448
00:24:52.780 --> 00:24:55.466
Pineapples on pizza? That's disgusting.

449
00:24:55.490 --> 00:24:58.080
Yeah. a disgusting trojan horse.

450
00:25:19.510 --> 00:25:20.810
Mind if I get something to eat?

451
00:25:22.350 --> 00:25:25.020
I'm just going right over there.
You can watch me the whole time.

452
00:25:35.110 --> 00:25:36.990
Kevin's shooter is here.

453
00:25:38.700 --> 00:25:41.490
No description. just a name. osiris.

454
00:25:42.540 --> 00:25:43.830
Anyone make sense?

455
00:25:46.790 --> 00:25:48.896
Well. this got exponentially worse.

456
00:25:48.920 --> 00:25:50.266
- Come with me.
- Hey.

457
00:25:50.290 --> 00:25:51.726
Yeah.

458
00:25:51.750 --> 00:25:55.130
Your patient just became my crime
scene. Let's see what we can find out.

459
00:26:00.890 --> 00:26:02.116
That looks pretty fresh to me.

460
00:26:02.140 --> 00:26:04.520
Yeah. it could have happened
when he fell or in a struggle.

461
00:26:05.390 --> 00:26:07.770
Why are you guys looking
at him? What's going on?

462
00:26:08.350 --> 00:26:10.586
Nakia. there's something
I need to tell you. all right?

463
00:26:10.610 --> 00:26:13.336
And what happens next depends
on your ability to stay calm.

464
00:26:13.360 --> 00:26:15.150
Focus on Kevin. like us.

465
00:26:17.650 --> 00:26:18.660
Good.

466
00:26:20.570 --> 00:26:22.740
Who'd you sell Kevin's
gaming system to?

467
00:26:23.370 --> 00:26:25.700
Why? Why are you asking now?

468
00:26:27.540 --> 00:26:31.436
I want you to look at that room.
tell me if you see anyone familiar.

469
00:26:31.460 --> 00:26:34.170
Can you do that for
me? Nice and casual.

470
00:26:43.180 --> 00:26:45.866
I don't know any of these
people. Why are you asking?

471
00:26:45.890 --> 00:26:47.430
Hey. will. check this out.

472
00:26:48.480 --> 00:26:50.166
That's skin under the nails.

473
00:26:50.190 --> 00:26:52.360
We're looking for someone
with scratch marks.

474
00:26:53.270 --> 00:26:56.376
Somebody better start telling
me what the hell is going on.

475
00:26:56.400 --> 00:26:58.110
Nice and easy. all right?

476
00:26:59.200 --> 00:27:04.830
We have reason to believe that the
person who did this to your son is here.

477
00:27:05.830 --> 00:27:08.476
Hey. hey. nakia. we're
staying calm. remember?

478
00:27:08.500 --> 00:27:09.710
Come on. come on back.

479
00:27:12.330 --> 00:27:16.106
I'm right here with you. okay? Now
come on. nakia. point the gun at me.

480
00:27:16.130 --> 00:27:19.066
I can keep Kevin safe. but I'm
gonna need you to let me do my job.

481
00:27:22.970 --> 00:27:25.986
Kevin?

482
00:27:26.010 --> 00:27:27.656
- What's going on?
- Rosen.

483
00:27:27.680 --> 00:27:29.206
- What do you need?
- Secure his tube now.

484
00:27:29.230 --> 00:27:31.076
bolus 50 fent. start a Propofol drip.

485
00:27:31.100 --> 00:27:32.876
Grab restraints. hold his arms down.

486
00:27:32.900 --> 00:27:34.956
Kevin. Kevin. there's a
tube down your throat.

487
00:27:34.980 --> 00:27:38.006
I need you to stay still so I can give you
medicine that's gonna relax you. okay?

488
00:27:38.030 --> 00:27:40.716
- It's okay. You're okay. I'm right here.
- His BP is tanking.

489
00:27:40.740 --> 00:27:43.660
- Yeah.
- What's going on? Kevin!

490
00:27:45.740 --> 00:27:48.726
He's losing consciousness
again. Did we push the prop?

491
00:27:48.750 --> 00:27:50.686
Bottom out his pressure?
Did his tube shift?

492
00:27:50.710 --> 00:27:53.436
- No. I haven't touched his sedation.
- All right.

493
00:27:53.460 --> 00:27:54.840
Breathing sounds are good.

494
00:27:57.210 --> 00:27:58.590
He's not seizing anymore.

495
00:27:59.170 --> 00:28:00.896
You said you could save him.

496
00:28:00.920 --> 00:28:03.276
You need to let them do their
job. They know what they're doing.

497
00:28:03.300 --> 00:28:04.720
All right. hold c-spine.

498
00:28:08.220 --> 00:28:10.406
- Whoa. Heavy hemorrhaging from the GSW.
- My god.

